      • getFileUploadtype

        public java.lang.String getFileUploadtype()
        Method to get the file upload type which can be ONSELECT or ONSUBMIT. ONSELECT indicates the file needs to be uploaded as soon as the file is registered . ONSUBMIT indicates the file will have to be uploaded to the server before API which persists the File in DB is called
        Returns:
        file upload type

      • isModelUpdateReqd

        public boolean isModelUpdateReqd()
        Method to indicate if Platform infrastructure has to update the underlying data model after the file is uploaded to the server. Data model update is required for the API call which persists the file in the DB. Platform can update the model, only if the file is uploaded from a text control or from a table column. And also the control has to be used to upload files for a single entity(table)
        Returns:
        true if the model update has to be done by default by Platform, false if the application wants to do the update

      • setModelUpdateReqd

        public void setModelUpdateReqd(boolean modelUpdateReqd)

Data model update is required for the API call which persists the file in the DB. Platform can update the model, only if the file is uploaded from a text control or from a table column. And also the control has to be used to upload files for a single entity(table)
        Parameters:
